<p class="dropcap">Most websites frustrate users and make businesses lose sales because the content takes too much time to load.</p>

<h3>Heavy assets ruins your website</h3>

<p>Heavy images, fonts, scripts and code-base are often responsible for increasing the page load time and damaging performance and UX.</p> 

<h3>Tips to improve performance</h3>

<p>A good way to optimise your website for performance is to optimise your images, code, script and fonts by following some basic best practices.</p>

<p>Performance should be a key aspect of your design process and useful to enhance the user-experience.</p>


      <h3>Checklist</h3>
      <h4 class="text-grey-color">Basics for optimising your interfaces for better performance.</h4>
        
         <ol class="special-list special-list--checklist bg-white-color">
             <li>Did we optimise the loading of our main CSS file?</li>
             <li>Did we optimise our image formats?</li>
             <li>Did we optimise our responsive images?</li>
             <li>Did we prioritise the loading of our resources <em>(e.g images, video, fontsâ€¦)</em>? </li>
             <li>Did we optimise our fonts?</li>
